Configure the radiator for Core Cooling in the VAB

20 hours ago, FreeThinker said:

Although Nanolathing itself does not unlock any new KSPI-E parts, it does improve the the performance off all graphite based radiator by 60%. In the future I will add a technode placeholder to make this clear

Well that is annoying, I wish I had known before I put up a couple of very heavy power generation sats as I was heavily heat limited.

There is no mention of that tech in the original post.  Where else would I have heard about that upgrade?

Edited June 13, 2016 by Liquid5n0w
What exactly are the "Start engineEMI" and "Start enginePulse" controls on the magneto inertial fusion engine good for? Also why does it seem to have a non functional thermal nozzle module?

1 hour ago, Liquid5n0w said:

Well that is annoying, I wish I had known before I put up a couple of very heavy power generation sats as I was heavily heat limited.

There is no mention of that tech in the original post.  Where else would I have heard about that upgrade?

I'm sorry for that. It used to be in the first post but it must have fallen off durring the transition. I added a new table with all technologies that affect radiator performance.

Note that Nanolathing originaly was the technodes which allowed you to upgrade radiators, only latter it became a specialized upgrade tech. Radiators used to start with a much lower maximum radiator temperature, but since radiator termperature scaled with power 4, temperature has a huge effect on radiator performance.

10 minutes ago, Liquid5n0w said:

Thanks for the table, it's very useful.

I'm confused though, I thought meta materials was an upgrade for the rads as well?

Yes it originally was but the performance increase between non upgraded radiator and upgraded radiators was insane, This was before CTT exisited. After CTT and thermal technodes became avialble, I spread out the performance increase using the thermal control technodes to determine maximum radiator temperature. On average every upgrade improves performance by 50%.

Edited June 13, 2016 by FreeThinker

Hello again, I've got another question/problem I'm afraid.

I cannot work out how to upgrade parts. I've accepted a contract to test the Closed Cycle Gas Core Engine Upgrade landed at Kerbin and in the VAB there's only the standard Closed Cycle Gas Core Engine. When I build a vehicle with one of these then there's no upgrade option on it when I right-click. I've searched high and low, I've tried with a Kerbal on EVA, I've googled and looked on the Wiki but I can't find anything. I've double checked and I very definitely have Exotic Nuclear Propulsion researched.

How do I access the upgraded engines and reactors?

13 minutes ago, BoilingCold said:

Hello again, I've got another question/problem I'm afraid.

I cannot work out how to upgrade parts. I've accepted a contract to test the Closed Cycle Gas Core Engine Upgrade landed at Kerbin and in the VAB there's only the standard Closed Cycle Gas Core Engine. When I build a vehicle with one of these then there's no upgrade option on it when I right-click. I've searched high and low, I've tried with a Kerbal on EVA, I've googled and looked on the Wiki but I can't find anything. I've double checked and I very definitely have Exotic Nuclear Propulsion researched.

How do I access the upgraded engines and reactors?

I'm afraid this is unintended. You should never have recieved an offer to test the upgraded Closes Cycle Gas Core Reactor because it is not meant to be a playable part

The part is not visible when you make use of the standard filter extensions. But You can still acces the part by filtering on Manufacturer and then select WarpPlugin.

Edited June 13, 2016 by FreeThinker

7 minutes ago, FreeThinker said:

I'm afraid this is unintended. The part is not visible when you make use of the filter extension. But I heard it is still visible in the non filtered list which contain all parts. If you still can't find it, I would advice to cancel the contract

Aha, thank you   Found them in the 'Manufacturer' category of the filter extension. Unfortunately there's 2 Upgraded ones and no way to tell which is which, but a bit of trial and error got the desired result in the end.

Version 1.8.27 for Kerbal Space Program 1.1.2

Released on 2016-06-13

  • Fixed rescaling ISRU
  • Fixed HTP resource in ISRU
  • Fixed support for Near Future Electric with Alcubierre WarpDrive
  • Fixed Lightbulp tech placeholder being used for testing contracts
  • Added KSPI Resource extractor to Stock Radial Drill (made by Profit)
  • Disabled Radiator configuration options
